Jr. Creed Speaker, Joli St. Germain placed 2nd and is advancing to STATE!

Radio Broadcasting placed 5th in the Area team members are: Hollyn Carr, Kylie Curtoys, & Blaize Leatherwood.

Spanish Creed Speaker, Daisy Almazan placed 6th in the Area!

We are so excited about all of the success today! Congratulations to the Dublin FFA LDE teams and good luck to Joli at State!

post_text:
NASA Dublin Graduate!!!! Mark your calendars Friday, October 18th.

Travis Brown, Class of 1957, is a retired engineer who worked for NASA. Mr. Brown worked on some very interesting projects and won awards for his contributions in sending American astronauts into space.
Mr. Brown will be a guest speaker Friday, October 18th for the DISD 8th graders at 2:00 and Physics/WIT students at 3:00. A reception will follow in the library at the Secondary Campus from 4:00-5:30. The community is welcome to attend the reception and visit with Mr. Brown. He and his family will be attending the football game that evening.

The passing standard is APPROACHES GRADE LEVEL.

Important Notice

For the next three days Dublin ISD will be conducting active shooter training on its campuses. Monday will be at the elementary campus, Tuesday will be at the secondary campus, and Wednesday will be at the intermediate campus. Note that this training involves simulation weapons and simulation ammunition that sounds like real gunfire. Please be aware when around the campuses in the assigned day. This intense training will better prepare Dublin ISD to protect its students and staff. Any questions may be directed to the Superintendentâ€™s office at 445-3341
